>o,file.nam where o was the read/write/delete operation you wanted?  This
>was run on System 40 when it was a KA and resided in the basement of
>building 5.
>
Actually, it was FILE op,id,file.ext,...  The id allowed the operator
to pick your tape from the rack.  op could be C (check queue,) D (delete
file from tape,) L (create a file with a tape directory,) R (recall a
file from tape,) F (file a file to tape,) W (wait for pending requests
to complete,) and Z (zero tape directory and then same as F.)  Since disks
were small, you often kept both programs and data on DECtapes.  The above
command allowed a batch job to request the files it needed and put them
back thus avoiding disk usage charges if it finished before the system
job which calculated disk usage ran.

Ah, those were the days.

Sam




