Depands on what the users are doing, and how fast they're doing it and how
well the system is optimized for them:

For example Long Island Regional Instructional Computer Service:
<note, the configurations quoted are from my memory, which means possibly
faulty>

1970 - PDP-8I/16K core, 128K DF-01, 1 h/s PTR - 12 simultaneous users via
genuine Western Electric #103 DataPumps through Leasco-owned and maintained
accoustic couplers and ASR-33s, running a mixture of 'big' BASIC, FOCAL,
Fortran, TSS-8 assembler jobs. Maximum size of a model of John Conway's Life
under TSS-8 BASIC, 9x9 - fire up a glider and go out for lunch.

1971 KA-10, 256K core, 2x RP-02 2MWord disk packs <Memorex>, 8X TU-55, HS
PTP/PTR, above PDP-8/I turned into DCA-680 UART: 72 simultaneous users running
a mixture of Bell-103 compatible modems, terminals <ASR-33s stil predominate>
up to 300 baud. SYSTATS show periodic peak loads of about 93% of available
reasources. Terminal waiting of more than 5 seconds RARE, despite much work
done to patch security holes in TOPS-10, which show up regularly when several
hundred high-school hackers are attacking the system. BASIC performs at
full-speed when running 72X72 Life jobs and assorted other time draggers

late 1971 - MUX/leased line cuts down number of local modems,  user numbers
slowly rise above theoretical maximum of 72, though peak time loads are
reduced by greater accessability to terminals by students. Swapping disk
added.

1972 - More lines, more MUX'es +2 RP-02s, Still topping out at 95% system
reasources used despite an outrageous number of insane jobs. No real waiting
except for folks getting frustrated with ASR-33s. All are now versed in the
"major" ASR-33 repairs which can be made with 1 paper clip, 2-4 rubber bands
and Scotch Magic Mending Tape.

1973 - late - 256Kwrd core box arrives, along with a 9-track magtape.
Decwriters and Hazeltine 2000 series terminals begin to replace ASR-33s at
many lcoations. More modems running at Bell 212 standards. Still no overload.

1974-6 the single-CPU KA-10 maxes out, but despite jobs ranging from mammoth
