First, my credentials - I ported TOPS-10 to the KS-10 over the winter of 
1977-78, and wrote the disk service routine for the UBA (Unibus Adaptor) 
interfaced RM03 and RP06.  I see no reason any Unibus device can't be made to 
work with the KS-10. Just a small matter of programming. Are you planning on 
running TOPS-10 or TOPS-20 on your KS? Getting TOPS-20 to work with a new 
controller would be easier (assuming you have access to the sources) because 
of the page-only I/O. TOPS-10 would be more of a bear because of the way I/O 
can be split across discontinuous page boundaries, but at least the sources 
are more easily available. I seem to recall the key is to be found in a 
routine called "MAPIO" which may be located in FILIO (or perhaps in VMSER).

Oh yes, another potential problem just occured to me. You need some way to 
format the drives into 128 36-bit words. The RM03 and RP06 were set up to 
work in either PDP-11 or PDP-10 modes. If you have full RM02 emulation then 
this may be possible. I can't recall whether the RM02 had a 36-bit mode. The 
more I think about it the more I come up with potential problems, but can't 
think of any that are insurmountable. If you have specific questions don't 
hesitate to email me. I still have a warm spot in my heart for the KS.

