I can confirm that Peter's RM05 code for TOPS-20 works; it's the obvious,
trivial addition to the sources.  I run it on my 2020.  I never tried
TOPS-10's RM05 support. 

The more nasty job is to format the RM05 for PDP-10s.  You need to add (or
was it cut?) a jumper in the controller to get 18-bit mode, and you need
to modify the formatting program (DDRPI, DSRMA, FORMAT, KSFORM) to handle
it.  Peter hacked up DSRMA to know about RM05s.

Then, too, if you don't have 3-phase power you need to rewrite the power
supply in the the RM05 to use the correct transformer tap for 240V instead
of 208V.  It'll run without you doing this....for a few months until the
power supply burns out...

